<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 06 at 8:06PM CST  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Christian
and northern Stone Counties through 830 PM CST...
At 806 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Crane, or 10 miles southeast of Aurora, moving northeast at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Nixa...                           Ozark...
Clever...                         Crane...
Highlandville...                  Fremont Hills...
Hurley...                         Spokane...
Selmore...                        Christian Center...
Ponce de Leon...                  Linden...
Boaz...                           Elsey...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
